    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 767.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">London,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25,</hi> 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> A telegram was received at this legation
                            yesterday, at one o’clock p. m., from the consular agent at Dover,
                            announcing the arrival of the steamer Niagara, on her way to Antwerp.
                            The Georgia had been taken and sent as prize to the United States. The
                            crew were landed at Dover.</p>
                <p>This event has made some sensation here. The newspapers express opinions
                            based on little information, and prompted by their respective
                            predilections in our struggle. Should any official indication be made
                            visible in the Times to-morrow morning I shall send a copy with the
                            despatch.</p>
                <p>I am your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
